				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It is a damn shame that guy died. It is a damn shame that he felt he had to take his life for what ever reason but this is not due to any one game. If he had been into Pokemon cards and killed himself this broad would be after Bandi for cash. Now I myself and many others that I know and respect play this game. Is it somewhat addictive ... yes. Has it lead to:<BR>
<BR>
 &quot;Scattered dirty clothes, fast-food wrappers, dozens of empty pizza boxes and chicken bones thrown haphazardly to the floor.&quot; and a gun to any of our heads... Hell no!<BR>
<BR>
This is because I and the people that I know do not have pre existing mental conditions. This guy was pledged by depression and it was a matter of time before something... anything... set him off. <BR>
<BR>
Let&#8217;s not forget that he left no suicide note and the only reason that they speculate that his suicide was EQ related at all was the fact that he had player&#8217;s names written down in his apartment. Well La dee da! He also had fast food crap all around him and up and quit his job a week earlier.... could it me that fat in the food along with carcinogens caused his suicidal behavior? Perhaps she should sue McDonald's or Pizza Hut. Maybe it was the fact that things were bad and work and he had no idea how he was going to pay the rent.... hmmm money pressure leads to suicide???? Naaah too far fetched. <BR>
<BR>
Point being that there are more than 430,000 registered players worldwide that play EQ and there is ONE (1) case of some guy shooting himself who happened to play the game.<BR>
<BR>
As I said before this guy had problems way before he ever started playing EQ. If his mother wants to lay blame on someone she needs to start by looking in the mirror and asking if there was something she should have done while he was under her roof.<BR>
<BR>
/rude the bible thumping mom <BR>
<BR>

